This directory holds all input, output, and history files for dmarc_reporter.py.

INPUT FILES — place these here before running the script:
  <prefix>_source.csv     One row per source IP: IP address, message count,
                          base domain (rDNS base, used as the join key),
                          and country code.
  <prefix>_spf.csv        SPF results per rDNS base domain: header-from (spoofed
                          domain), envelope-from, SPF result, SPF aligned, and
                          Reverse DNS Base (join key).
  <prefix>_dkim.csv       DKIM results per rDNS base domain: header-from (spoofed
                          domain), DKIM selector, DKIM domain, DKIM result, DKIM
                          aligned, and Reverse DNS Base (join key).

  The prefix is the date string you pass on the command line, e.g. 2MAY2026.
  Join key: source["Base Domain"] == spf/dkim["Reverse DNS Base"]

OUTPUT FILES — written by the script:
  <prefix>_full.csv       Correlated report: all three input files joined on
                          Base Domain / Reverse DNS Base, enriched with live
                          rDNS and WHOIS data (abuse email, RIR, org, ASN).
  Report_History.csv      Persistent record of the last date each IP was reported.
                          Used to enforce the 30-day cooldown between reports for
                          the same IP. Created automatically on the first run.

NOTE: All *.csv files are excluded from version control. Only this file is committed.
